items.name: Immodest Muff (Pretend Dick)
items.description:
A LoRA for creating a pose where a woman holds an oblong object like it's a dick. Training data is mostly 512x768. I've found that lowering the fruit/vegetable weight to 0.8-0.9 helps to prevent tons of them from being added to the image. SD 1.5 models have trouble with hands, as you know, so it may take a few tries to get a good looking image. Weights between 0.8-0.9 seem to work best, though I've found that lowering the LoRA weight by 0.05-0.1 when using Realistic Vision models leads to better results.

Reliable foods:

  • banana

  • eggplant

  • cucumber

  • carrot*

*For some reason, "carrot" produces weird results unless you lower the weight to around (carrot:0.8). Even then carrots are weird.

Example prompt: a photo of a naked woman holding (a banana:0.9), immodest_muff <lora:immodest_muff:0.8>

items.name: Colorful Horrors
items.description:
This, like it's main merge (Eerie Mix of Decay by @Fanta_sea), makes a wide range of creepy creatures that fuel nightmares. But now you can add color prompts and the colors that show up are incredibly vibrant.

How to use recommendations:

- Dimensions: 768x512 or 512x768

- Positive Prompt: Terms related to horror (horror, zombies, bloody, demonic, frightening, etc) and terms related to color (Vibrant, colorful, neon, glowing, psychedelic, etc).

- Negative Prompt: I used Bad Dream and FastNegativeV2 negative embeds.

- Normally this model does pretty well with faces without help or prompting, however if you run into specific face issues, aDetailer is an easy way to bring quality back to faces.

- VAE: I did not bake a vae into this model, but I used kl-f8-anime2 vae for all the pictures for the model.

- Clip Skip, Sampling Methods, Sampling Steps, CFG Scale: Please refer to the pictures posted with the model near the end, I posted pics that show those ranges and how it affect the creations of this model. Wide range though, play around.

Credit:
Eerie Mix of Decay by @Fanta_sea
3dToonScape by @Fanta_sea

items.name: Asakura Mami (Semi-Original Character)
items.description:
"Mami never appears in the series; she is only mentioned by Tatsuji Chibiki in Episode 6."

From the Another Wiki.

Faced with a difficult situation, I decided to fiddle with generating a character with the simple prompt of "Asakura, Mami". What I got was several recreations of Tomoe Mami from Madoka Magica... but also this girl with black hair. A Loab-like person that was present in the latent spaces of the algorithm that I had to break out.

And so, I went to work through various models and cherry picking pictures of a similar picture, then blended them together in the usual Colabs to create someone who, while she is named for a character in Another, is not really a character from Another. She is trapped inside this limbo of being canon and being fanon.

How fitting for an extra class member.

And then it didn't help matters when, while making another LoRA for an off-screen Extra, I ended up making some images for a new LoRA. I decided to give it to Mami and cite it as her, upon her return to the afterlife, instead reincarnating into another world as a miko.

items.name: Takamuran Style
items.description:
A scribble-like colorful style trained on the characters from the Takamuran circle hgames. LyCORIS version of previously released LoRA.

How to use
No trigger word needed. Just prompt 1girl or 1boy and go. The dataset contained a lot of monster girls (spiders, slime, fox etc) so that content should work fine. Also a lot of "muscular female", "dark-skinned female" and all kinds of bigger breasts sizes.
Approx 75%+ of the dataset is various levels of NSFW but after a bit of wrangling this LyCORIS also handles SFW.

Recommended sampler: DIMM, DPM++ 2M Karras or any other that doesn't "clean up" the results too much.
Recommended model: NAI or any other with good/better support for drawing styles like AOM3. For models with realism mixed in I recommend putting "3d" and "realistic" in negatives. Sample images are from AOM3.

Despite the dataset having little of it some models like to add speech bubbles, putting "speech bubbles" and "text" in negatives helps. You probably want to add "standing", "sitting" or any position since otherwise the many sexual positions from the dataset tend to blend through.

Misc
Trained on NAI at 512 resolution with a dataset of 413 images.
All images are untouched txt2img, no inpainting or helper embeddings used for quality transparence, e.g. - things should look even better if you do.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the circle if you want the good stuff.

items.name: DEN Collection
items.description:
So I wanted to get more use of all my inversions. this is nothing fancy but put together the wild cards for my style inversions and for the inversions in have made, allows me to randomly make instead of showing favouritism.

simple structured folder. folder for the textual inversions of the ladies, one for the styles, and one for the wild cards. thought I would put them all together as its easy way to get them all and also vary the use.

Use

Simple use. Extract the folder and put the inversions in your embeddings folder and the wild cards in the wildcards folder. The folders were just for ease and not necessary. You may only want the style or the girls. Figured easiest to separate.

Wildcards

If you aren't familiar, wild cards allow for random prompt use from a text file. The prompts are done by line and you trigger these with your prompt using __filename__ (that's double underscore each end). So if you use mine you would use either __dengirls__ or __denstyles__ in your prompt.

My wildcards here require the inversions as they have been named, so don't change the names or the wildcards won't work.

Making your own prompt files is easy. Ensure you have wildcards in your automatic1111 (link). Make a text file and name ot as you want *example hairstyles.txt). Line by line you can make prompts which will be randomly selected by the wildcard. put the wildcards file in the wildcards folder. You are done. Now just use __filename__ in your prompt when generating.

I recommend the prompt builder wildcards as they have been great if you don't want to make your own.

items.name: Nicki Nicole [LORA]
items.description:
V3.0 - v2.0

  1. Spanish:

He usado una nueva configuración para que el resultado sea mucho más realista. Trata de usar EpicRealism (pure Evolution v5).

Es posible que el nombre del LORA cambie, así que no lo copies directamente de CIVITAI, mejor selecciónalo del apartado de LORAS de Stable Diffusion para que no haya errores en la generación de imágenes.

Mi configuración usando EpicRealism:

  • Lora Strength: 1

  • Prompt: Explicación simple de la imagen (pruebe primero sin palabras clave adicionales)

    En el caso de esta Lora, el prompt debe comenzar con "A woman...".

  • Prompt negativo: cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2), asian, chinese, (epiCNegative:0.9)

  • Sampling steps: >20 (si la imagen tiene errores o artefactos, use steps más altos)

  • CFG Scale: 5

  • Sampling method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Tamaño: 512x768 o 768x512

  • Hires fix: 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G (Denoising strenght: 0.35, Upscale by: 2)

  1. English:

I have used a new configuration so that the result is much more realistic. Try using EpicRealism (pure Evolution v5).

It is possible that the name of the LORA will change, so do not copy it directly from CIVITAI, rather select it from the LORAS section of Stable Diffusion so that there are no errors in the generation of images.

My setup using EpicRealism:

  • Lora Strength: 1 ( Example: <lora:nickinicole-08:1> )

  • Prompt: simple explanation of the image (try first without extra keywords)

    In the case of this LORA, the prompt must begin with "A woman...".

  • Negative prompt: cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2), asian, chinese, (epiCNegative:0.9)

  • Sampling steps: >20 (if image has errors or artefacts use higher Steps)

  • CFG Scale: 5

  • Sampling method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Size: 512x768 or 768x512

  • Hires fix: 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G (Denoising strength: 0.35, Upscale by: 2)

V1.0

Lora Strength: 0.8 - 0.9 ( Start with 0.8 )

This LORA has been trained with the Photon model.

Follow the indications of the model to have a good result. (If it takes you to load the CIVITAI pages like me, I leave it here below):

  • Prompt: A simple sentence in natural language describing the image.

    In the case of this Lora, the prompt must begin with "a woman...". Better separately: "A woman, (the rest of the indications),...

  • Negative: "cartoon, painting, illustration, (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:2)"

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras | Steps: 25 | CFG Scale: 6

  • Clip Skip 2

  • Size: 512x768 or 768x512

  • Hires.fix: 4x-UltraSharp | steps: 10 | Denoising: 0.45 | Upscale x 2

(avoid using negative embeddings unless absolutely necessary)
